VESICULAR STOMATITIS - USA
**************************
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 1997 13:57:09 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
Via: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Text of a fax received on 14 July 1997 from Dr J.M. Arnoldi, Deputy
Administrator, Veterinary Services, United States Department of Agriculture,
Washington, DC
See also: 11 July 1997, 4 July 1997, 20 June 1997, 13 June 1997
End of previous report period: 7 July 1997
End of this report period: 14 July 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Bernalillo County, State of New Mexico 4
Dona Ana County, State of New Mexico 2
Sandoval County, State of New Mexico 8
Valencia County, State of New Mexico 2
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: Thirty-two (32).
Description of affected population in new outbreaks: horses of various breeds.
Total number of animals (all equids) in the new outbreaks:
susceptible 47
cases 13
deaths 0
destroyed 0
slaughtered 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Services
Laboratory.
B. Diagnostic tests used: positive ELISA with compatible signs.
C. Causal agent: vesicular stomatitis virus, type Indiana.
Epidemiology: investigations pending; case control study in progress.
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine placed on affected
premises by the State of New Mexico.
---
Dorothy B. Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
ProMED-AHEAD Program Officer http://www.fas.org/promed/
Federation of American Scientists http://www.fas.org/ahead/
V 202-675-1011 F: 202-675-1010
